(1044, 1, '2014-06-19 18:49:15', '2014-06-19 11:49:15', '<h2>DIVISION</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.	Organization Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nBased on results of the 15th Perbanas Congress held in 2003 and the reached agreement of the Perbanas Board Meeting on 31 March 2004, functions which have to be carried out by the organization sector are:\r\n•	Ensure the organization runs according to the Articles of Association of Perbanas. \r\n•	Socialize membership and increase the members of Perbanas.\r\n•	Develop activities of the organization.\r\n•	Improve the role of Perbanas in its relations with state institutions as well as private institutions, among them the House of Representatives, Bank Indonesia, Chamber of Commerce, and other institutions.\r\n•	Hold plenary meetings conducted alternatingly in each region which require attention and hold congress once in every three years.\r\n•	Represent the Chairman, together with the secretariat general, as a representative of the organization in or outside the court.\r\n•	Socialize the Five Ethics of Perbanas and implement good corporate governance (GCG) among all members.\r\n•	Cooperate with Bankers Club Indonesia (BCI), Institut Bankir Indonesia (IBI), and Himpunan Bank-Bank Negara (Himbara) to implement an accreditation system for banking professions, referring to best practice in the world of international banking. \r\nPrograms which have been successfully conducted by the organization sector under the leadership of Jahja Setiaatmadja:\r\n•	Routine member meetings\r\n•	Sports and arts events\r\n•	Golf tournaments\r\n•	Plenary meetings\r\n•	Socialization of Perbanas membership\r\n•	Socialization of the Five Ethics of Perbanas and GCG\r\n•	Perbanas 16th Congress\r\n\r\n<h3>2.	International Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nThe international sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Actively participate in international forums as an ambassador of Perbanas.\r\n•	Represent Perbanas in the ASEAN Finance Corporation (AFC).\r\n•	Develop relations with international institutions, such as IMF, World Bank, IDFC, ADB, IDB, rating agencies, and other international institutions, in order to improve assessment towards the national banking industry.\r\n•	Provide information on national banking, specifically on Perbanas, to the international public who inquire.\r\n•	Socialize international programs which are available for the banking industry in Indonesia, specifically for Perbanas.\r\n•	Perform benchmark studies towards the banking landscape, mergers, and banking rehabilitation programs in other countries, especially those which have experienced a post crisis period. \r\n•	Formulate and socialize guidelines for best practice, which is needed by the national banking industry in anticipation towards global issues, such as risk management, technology, branding and image, and GCG.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully conducted by the international sector under the leadership of Andi M. Hatta.\r\n•	On 17-19 March 2004, Perbanas attended the Lafferty Retail Finance Asia Pacific 2004 Conference and Expo in Bangkok, Thailand.\r\n•	On 26 May 2004, Perbanas met with the Director of the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office.\r\n•	On 16-18 September 2004, representing Perbanas, the international sector attended the 15th ASEAN Banking Conference and the 34th ASEAN Banking Council Meeting in Cebu, Philippines.\r\n•	On 9 September 2004, Perbanas reached a memorandum of understanding (MOU) with the Asian Institute Management (AIM).\r\n•	Head of the international sector conducted a meeting with Worlds Bank, represented by Djauhari Sitorus, financial analyst, together with Emiko Todoraki and John McDowel from the AML/CFT Team, Washington DC.\r\n•	The international sector conducted discussions on credit bureau formats with several international forums.\r\n\r\n<h3>3.	Regional Relations Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nThe Regional Relations Sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Publish newsletters and a website which can be accessed by all members of Perbanas. \r\n•	Conduct and ensure smooth communication between the central committee and regional committee.\r\n•	Announce up to date information and work programs of the central office to regional offices. \r\n•	Regular visits to regional offices through members who are visiting their branch offices. \r\n•	Accommodate and assist in solving regional issues.\r\n•	Monitor the activities and work programs of regional offices. \r\n•	Assist in optimizing regional activities through training and seminars.\r\n•	Form good relations between the central committee and regional stakeholders through roadshows/courtesy visits, informal meetings, and other programs.\r\n•	Organize Perbanas regional plenary meetings.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully conducted by the regional relations sector under the leadership of L.G. Rompas:\r\n•	Publishing of written newsletters and continuous website updates.\r\n•	Formation of Perbanas regional committees.\r\n•	Visits to Perbanas regional offices.\r\n•	Organizing Perbanas regional plenary meetings.\r\n•	Monitor the activities and work programs of regional offices.\r\n\r\n<h3>4.	Education and Human Resource Development Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nThe education and human resource development sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Improve the quality of human resources among members of Perbanas.\r\n•	Improve the role of STIE Perbanas and STIMIK Perbanas in the national banking industry. \r\n•	Conduct workshops and training on banking activities.\r\n•	Assess rules and regulations on employment which are applicable or will be applied.  \r\n•	Assist the needs of members in facing problems concerning employment.\r\n•	Provide banking profession certification programs in cooperation with other associations (BCI and IBI) to anticipate future competition and globalization. \r\n•	Conduct research activities on the subject of human resources, such as competency requirement surveys, remuneration, and curriculum.\r\n•	Prepare STIE Perbanas and STIMIK Perbanas as banking clinics or center of excellence for the national banking industry.\r\n•	Utilize Perbanas website as a media for information on human resource matters, such as information on courses, seminars, and job vacancies.\r\n•	Promote STIE Perbanas to members by delegating Perbanas members to visit STIE Perbanas and recommending graduates of STIE Perbanas to work at member banks.\r\n•	Initiate a banking Master of Management (MM) or risk management program at STIE Perbanas in cooperation with national as well as international institutions.\r\n•	Conduct curriculum assessment based on the needs of the banking industry.\r\n•	Organize seminars as a profit center for the central committee.\r\n•	Provide scholarships.\r\n•	Provide consultation services.\r\n\r\nPrograms which have been successfully implemented by the education and human resource development sector under the leadership of Pramukti Surjaudaja:\r\n•	Marketing of STIE and STIMIK Perbanas to all members.\r\n•	Organizing job expos for graduates of STIE and STIMIK Perbanas.\r\n•	Assessment towards the curriculums of STIE and STIMIK Perbanas through workshops.\r\n•	Conduct advisory programs concerning human resource matters.\r\n•	Provide MM and risk management programs at STIE Perbanas.\r\n•	Provide scholarship programs.\r\n•	Organizing seminars which are profit oriented.\r\n•	Publishing information on human resources on the official website of Perbanas.\r\n\r\n<h3>5.	Assessment on Banking and Law Sector</h3>\r\n \r\nThe assessment on banking and law sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Conduct assessments on policies as well as from a legal aspect, towards laws which apply or are still being formulated.\r\n•	Create and coordinate activities of ad hoc commission which are formulated to improve assessment towards issues concerning Perbanas.\r\n•	Coordinate with an appointed expert team to resolve common strategic and analytic issues on banking.\r\n•	Offer input and assessment to law makers.\r\n•	Socialize the assessments that have been made to members of Perbanas and the general public.\r\n•	Ensure the legal aspects of the organization’s activities are in line with the Articles of Association and according to the laws which apply.\r\n•	Assist members who need assistance on legal banking.\r\n•	Conduct arbitration and advocacy if needed, in order to assist in the settlement of a dispute among Perbanas members.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully implemented by the assessment on banking and law sector, based on its above functions:\r\n•	Form a working commission responsible for conducting assessments on the payment system, know your customer (KYC) and consumer protection, taxes, Indonesian Banking Architecture (API), good corporate governance (GCG), as well as risk management. \r\n•	Provide regular as well as incidental assessment and recommendations.\r\n•	Form an expert team in coordination with academics to assist the committee when conducting assessments towards a certain issue.\r\n•	Create an advocacy and arbitration agency among members and between members and their clients.\r\n\r\n<h3>6.	Public Relations Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nThe public relations sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Form good relations with the press and analysts in order to improve the image of Perbanas, as well as spread accurate information on Perbanas specifically, and the national banking industry in general.\r\n•	Organize press conferences, roadshows and public exposures regularly.\r\n•	Provide information to the press and analysts on the performance of Perbanas. \r\n•	Maintain the Perbanas website to keep it up to date, informative and attractive. \r\n•	Form good relations with Perbanas stakeholders through community development programs such as public relations, donations or charity, and sponsorship.\r\n•	Create a business incubator program which connects the banking industry with the development of small and micro businesses (UMKM).\r\n•	Develop an environmentally friendly banking concept, which is ‘green banking’.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully implemented by the public relations sector under the leadership of Winny E. Hassan:\r\n•	News release and media briefings.\r\n•	Updating the Perbanas website.\r\n•	Establishment of UKM Centers in every region, involving Perbanas regional committees. \r\n•	Nature and culture preservation programs.\r\n•	Press tours\r\n•	Roadshows and public exposure\r\n\r\n<h3>7.	Financial Sector</h3>\r\n\r\nThe financial sector assumes the following functions:\r\n•	Ensure transparent and responsible financial administration.\r\n•	Conduct annual auditing with an appointed accounting office.\r\n•	Publish Perbanas financial reports for all members every three months.\r\n•	Optimize investment of Perbanas funds, including the Yayasan Perbanas fund. \r\n•	Assist in improving the financial systems of Yayasan Perbanas, STIE Perbanas, STIMIK Perbanas, and Perbanas regional offices.\r\n•	Assess member fees and other financial sources for fund raising.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully implemented by the financial sector under the leadership of Lisawati:\r\n•	Publish regular financial reports for all members through newsletters and website. \r\n•	Assessment of member fees and other financial sources for fund raising.\r\n•	Auditing of financial report by a public accountant’s office.\r\n\r\n<h3>8.	Secretariat General</h3>\r\n\r\nFunctions of the secretariat general are as follows:\r\n•	Coordinate activities of the secretariat in providing assistance to all sectors and Perbanas regional offices.\r\n•	Maintain work continuity of the Perbanas organization in accordance to the mandate of the congress and Articles of Association of Perbanas.\r\n•	Strengthen and improve the relationship among members as well as between members and the Perbanas executive board.\r\n•	Offer the best service to Perbanas members and the public in providing data and information.\r\n•	Provide a help desk for Perbanas members to convey the problems they are facing among members or between members and other institutions.\r\n•	Accompany the Chairman or Head of Organization in representing Perbanas.\r\n•	Organize board meetings and together with the organization sector, conduct plenary meetings and Perbanas Congress.\r\nPrograms which have been successfully implemented by the secretariat general under the leadership of Danny Hartono:\r\n•	Organize meetings:\r\n-	Executive Board meetings every two weeks.\r\n-	General Board meetings every month.\r\n-	General Board meetings with the Advisory Council every three months.\r\n•	Conduct member meetings in cooperation with the organization sector. \r\n\r\n<h2>WORKING GROUP</h2>\r\n\r\n', 'How We Work', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '419-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-19 18:49:15', '2014-06-19 11:49:15', '', 419, 'http://localhost/perbanas/en/419-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
